commit_message:
Don't send heartbeats if Manager reports a problem

This commit adds is_working method to base Manager class that can be
used to indicate that service has some problems and isn't running
correctly. This is used to block refreshing Service heartbeats if
Manager will return False from is_working.

The method is implemented in c-vol Manager to return initialization
state of the underlying volume driver.

Closes-Bug: 1446750
DocImpact

Change-Id: I809b2b777a0f84d12f39f2233920ec961f74f846

commit_message:
Add unique_values constraint

This constraint ensures that lists or dictionaries contain unique
values.

For instance, [1,2,3,4] and {'a':1, 'b': 2} would pass this constraint's
validation; while [1,1,2] and {'a':1, 'b': 1} wouldn't pass it.

Related-Bug: #1740396
Change-Id: I2436512c5bb1a2574457b86094b74ea3f9cab72f

subject: Improve conditionals to reduce failures
messages: [{'account_id': 6816, 'date': '2018-03-11 18:29:32.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 1.'}, {'account_id': 17799, 'date': '2018-03-11 19:13:44.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Code-Review+2'}, {'account_id': 7353, 'date': '2018-03-14 05:34:42.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Workflow+1 Code-Review+2'}]
revisions:
[{'created': '2018-03-11 18:29:32.000000000', 'message': 'Improve conditionals to reduce failures

The conditionals based on nspawn_config_exists.stat.exists
fail in some conditions. When the task doing the state does
not execute, there is no dictionary result with the appropriate
structure, causing tasks relying on the structure to fail.

This patch re-arranges the conditionals so that when they
are evaluated, they do so in a better process of elimination.
First, evaluate the same conditional as the stat task, then
validate that the stat dict exists, then check the key in
the stat result.

Change-Id: I6f2d8943c4279edf44907aa145935be858dbc673
'}]
commit_message:
Improve conditionals to reduce failures

The conditionals based on nspawn_config_exists.stat.exists
fail in some conditions. When the task doing the state does
not execute, there is no dictionary result with the appropriate
structure, causing tasks relying on the structure to fail.

This patch re-arranges the conditionals so that when they
are evaluated, they do so in a better process of elimination.
First, evaluate the same conditional as the stat task, then
validate that the stat dict exists, then check the key in
the stat result.

Change-Id: I6f2d8943c4279edf44907aa145935be858dbc673

  pipeline and retry settings or nerfing the build via ansible fork lowering
  to work around it. This is an old issue that we normally put a more

commit_message:
Fix Ssh connection issues on openstack-ansible-ops mnaio builds

  We normally see ssh connection issues during the lxc container setup
  portion of OSA builds. Most people usually end up tweaking ansible ssh
  pipeline and retry settings or nerfing the build via ansible fork lowering
  to work around it. This is an old issue that we normally put a more
  permanent fix in our physical environments by setting the ssh maxsessions
  and maxstartups. On the mnaio builds I have been working around this by
  stopping the build before deployment and making the changes in a script.

Change-Id: I54c223e1fb9edf6947bc7f76ff689bad22456420
Closes-Bug: 1752914

subject: Enable mutable config in ZUN
revisions:
[{'created': '2018-03-12 11:12:01.000000000', 'message': "Enable mutable config in ZUN

New releases of oslo.config support a 'mutable' parameter to Opts.
This is only respected when the new method mutate_config_files is
called instead of reload_config_files. ZUN delegates making this call
to oslo.service, so how do we switch?

Icec3e664f3fe72614e373b2938e8dee53cf8bc5e allows services to tell
oslo.service they want mutate_config_files to be called by passing a
parameter, which this patch does.

This allows ZUN to benefit from
I1e7a69de169cc85f4c09954b2f46ce2da7106d90, where the 'debug' option

we should be able to turn debug logging on and off by changing the

Change-Id: I50458a450f7931a5b606147beb22ef406d73ae49
"}]
commit_message:
Enable mutable config in ZUN

New releases of oslo.config support a 'mutable' parameter to Opts.
This is only respected when the new method mutate_config_files is
called instead of reload_config_files. ZUN delegates making this call
to oslo.service, so how do we switch?

Icec3e664f3fe72614e373b2938e8dee53cf8bc5e allows services to tell
oslo.service they want mutate_config_files to be called by passing a
parameter, which this patch does.

This allows ZUN to benefit from
I1e7a69de169cc85f4c09954b2f46ce2da7106d90, where the 'debug' option
(owned by oslo.log) is made mutable. IE when all these patches merge,
we should be able to turn debug logging on and off by changing the
config and sending SIGHUP.

Part of bp:mutable-config

Change-Id: I50458a450f7931a5b606147beb22ef406d73ae49

When I enbaled ovn_worker for the tests, they are randomly failing
while creating segmenthostmappings(bug 1753657). The error(i.e
foreign key constraint failed) shows segment missing in DB(or not
yet commited to DB) while adding segmenthostmappings. So I changed
subscribing for SEGMENT resource from PRECOMMIT_CREATE to AFTER_CREATE
event. With this change, I ran tests several times and they are
consistently passing.

Closes-bug: #1753657

commit_message:
l3ha: Update router gateway port binding

In reference implementation, user can check HA master router host
in two ways
1) CLI l3-agent-list-hosting-router (As OVN doesn't support agents,
   it can't implement this CLI)
2) router gateway port binding - Router gateway port's host will
   reflect the master router host.
OVN driver supports second approach i.e it will update router
gateway port binding to active host and users can use this
information to find master router host.

When I enbaled ovn_worker for the tests, they are randomly failing
while creating segmenthostmappings(bug 1753657). The error(i.e
foreign key constraint failed) shows segment missing in DB(or not
yet commited to DB) while adding segmenthostmappings. So I changed
subscribing for SEGMENT resource from PRECOMMIT_CREATE to AFTER_CREATE
event. With this change, I ran tests several times and they are
consistently passing.

Closes-bug: #1753657
Change-Id: Iddd2da546c4cabe743a2eabca36fcdb5103f068f

The cinder_sudoers entry in the cinder configmap-etc was consuming

Change-Id: I214912b3ed4185a201f4f94e82eaa50d6d321018

commit_message:
Cinder: Fix sudoers reference in configmap

The cinder_sudoers entry in the cinder configmap-etc was consuming
the neutron_sudoers entry in the values.yaml. This corrects it to
point at cinder_sudoers instead

Change-Id: I214912b3ed4185a201f4f94e82eaa50d6d321018

commit_message:
Add release note for updated enabled file in rocky

Enabled file for template generator is updated a lot to remove all of
embedded JS copies from the repo.  The latest eanble file does not have
compatibility with stable/queens heat-dashboard, therefore it is better
to have heads-up for users to re-copy it to
horizon/openstack_dashboard/enabled when they need to update
heat-dashboard from queens to rocky.

Change-Id: Ifdc29d95e93379cda1d12367329e37c885ddcef2

revisions:
[{'created': '2018-03-08 14:31:06.000000000', 'message': "ovsfw: Use bundle when adding security group rules

Sometimes ports can have a lot of security group rules. Adding OpenFlow
rules to the integration bridge can be a bottle neck when bundle option
is not used.

As OVS firewall currently uses CLI interface, the bundle support is
implemented only for that. The native interface has on-going work but
before we switch completely to the native, we can benefit from bundle
option now.

e.g. when adding 100 000 flows the bundle option takes the time down
from ~10 seconds to 1 seconds. So it's about 10 times faster.

Change-Id: I1feaeb659c8badf23230e36145235d49d50b6bfb
(cherry picked from commit b3b2df142e5906a1da0c8c9b2cfb3a60a6527e77)
"}]
commit_message:
ovsfw: Use bundle when adding security group rules

Sometimes ports can have a lot of security group rules. Adding OpenFlow
rules to the integration bridge can be a bottle neck when bundle option
is not used.

As OVS firewall currently uses CLI interface, the bundle support is
implemented only for that. The native interface has on-going work but
before we switch completely to the native, we can benefit from bundle
option now.

e.g. when adding 100 000 flows the bundle option takes the time down
from ~10 seconds to 1 seconds. So it's about 10 times faster.

Change-Id: I1feaeb659c8badf23230e36145235d49d50b6bfb
(cherry picked from commit b3b2df142e5906a1da0c8c9b2cfb3a60a6527e77)

When rules are passed to update() method of firewall, it translates
protocol in case it was passed as a string to integer. This can cause a
side-effect in testing when same set of rules is passed multiple times.
Securiry group rules always have a string in protocol field.

commit_message:
ovs-fw: Don't modify passed rules to update

When rules are passed to update() method of firewall, it translates
protocol in case it was passed as a string to integer. This can cause a
side-effect in testing when same set of rules is passed multiple times.
Securiry group rules always have a string in protocol field.

Change-Id: I0d95c6c41ad3c4b52986307449d90f13bbd412ac
(cherry picked from commit 37aba76275fd9a867ac15aa5c503b602b469ff97)

I don't think we're ready to move forward with this quite yet, but when we do, at least the following need to be addressed:

- Traits in provider summaries is covered by https://review.openstack.org/#/c/517027/ (in flight).  This patch should be rebased on top of that subseries (at least).
- Microversion update - aside from needing to be made current wrt the actual microversion being published - also needs to include api-ref mods and a reno.
- It would be nice to coordinate with https://review.openstack.org/#/c/517757/ .  That guy will add the microversion for granular resource requests, a superset of what this patch is doing.  It wouldn't be a bad thing if we could publish just the one microversion."}, {'account_id': 5754, 'date': '2018-03-14 02:27:36.000000000', 'content': 'Abandoned'}]

placement: add traits to the 'GET /allocation_candidates' endpoint

This patch adds traits to the request and response of allocation
candidates endpoint in microversion 1.11

Co-Authored-By: leizhang <lei.a.zhang@intel.com>
Implement-blueprint add-trait-support-in-allocation-candidates
Change-Id: I94da52039d3a36870b8e24ac5236eedf773eb371

commit_message:
Add CRUD support for application credentials

Add support for creating, retrieving, and deleting application
credentials. Application credentials do not support updates.

In order to provide a positive user experience for the `--role` option,
this patch also includes an improvement to the
`identity.common._get_token_resource()` function that allows it to
introspect the roles list within a token. This way there is no need to
make a request to keystone to retrieve a role object, which would fail
most of the time anyway due to keystone's default policy prohibiting
unprivileged users from retrieving roles.

bp application-credentials

Change-Id: I29e03b72acd931305cbdac5a9ff666854d05c6d7

commit_message:
Fluentd: Change elasticsearch endpoint port and creds reference

Updates the fluent-logging chart to reference the elasticsearch
endpoint via lookups on the `http` port to match the elasticsearch
chart's handling of the client port.  This also updates the helm
test pod to reference the elasticsearch credentials via the
secret used elsewhere in the fluent-logging chart

Change-Id: I352d912db5e231e14dc58cdf897ae642f3256373

commit_message:
Modify the load order of manage.py

In zun.cmd.compute.py
Existing process:
1. Import the zun.compute.manager.py file
2. Load configuration item
3. Start the service
So if you use a timer like this:

    @periodic_task.periodic_task(run_immediately=True,
        spacing=CONF.detection_interval)
    def delete_unused_containers(self, context):

Modify the CONF.detection_interval will not take effect,
it is always using the default value

Change-Id: Ia3ca548690f67c010db20a675ae33df240868349
Closes-Bug: #1755095

revisions:
[{'created': '2018-02-23 11:36:00.000000000', 'message': '[Fullstack] Respawn dhclient process in case of error

When dhclient process is started as async process by fake machine resource,
it might happen that "None" will be returned as first line of output
from this process. This is treated as an error and dhclient is halted
immediately.
Because of that fake machine don't have configured IP address and
test fails.

This patch adds "respawn_timeout" value set to 5 seconds for dhclient
async process. When dhclient process is restarted it should works fine
and IP address should be then configured properly.

Change-Id: Ie056578abbe6e18c8415c6e61d755f2248a70541
Closes-Bug: #1728948
(cherry picked from commit 92959238a3e408e810ccd4f3d3d453a35afb5bba)
'}]
commit_message:
[Fullstack] Respawn dhclient process in case of error

When dhclient process is started as async process by fake machine resource,
it might happen that "None" will be returned as first line of output
from this process. This is treated as an error and dhclient is halted
immediately.
Because of that fake machine don't have configured IP address and
test fails.

This patch adds "respawn_timeout" value set to 5 seconds for dhclient
async process. When dhclient process is restarted it should works fine
and IP address should be then configured properly.

Change-Id: Ie056578abbe6e18c8415c6e61d755f2248a70541
Closes-Bug: #1728948
(cherry picked from commit 92959238a3e408e810ccd4f3d3d453a35afb5bba)

commit_message:
Add license for empty __init__.py

This also fix build-openstack-sphinx-docs, there was a change introduced
in sphinx 1.6.6:
https://github.com/sphinx-doc/sphinx/pull/4335/files

If the size of __init__.py is less than 2, then the module would be
skipped which will cause the sphinx consistency checking failing later.

Change-Id: I9d8764b6e907aceed8bb8a9b04711145d0eb32ad

commit_message:
Fix UTs to accommodate new_facade flag in OVO objects

In current UTs, in tests that do not actually touch databases,
we mock out refresh and expunge in current context. This will
not work under new engine facade, as new sessions are created
everytime.

We will need this fix when we set any object's new_facade flag
to True.

Closes-Bug: #1750735

Change-Id: I3a8bc06a671e37959e3014f8672b9a5e118c5c52

commit_message:
Fix network no-op driver get_network_configs

The network no-op driver was not returning the required data for a
get_network_configs call which causes load balancer failover tests to
fail when using the no-op driver.

Change-Id: I52b5651a7b33aae42760b850f913b6b591367207
(cherry picked from commit d1e9c56128da27acb8836de931699ae18fe7779a)

commit_message:
Cleanup error messages on failure

When test_server_commands_main_help() fails it dumps a ton of
unformatted text on an exception message. This commit attempts to clean
it up to make it easier to read.

commit_message:
Add tests for APTRepositoryCacheUpdateRule

The custom ansible-lint rule APTRepositoryCacheUpdateRule was added in
67bfc907030d7f0ce6fbb63f0608aa021f0b5400, this change adds tests to
validate its functionality.

Includes fix from 44761d390b9f9f4794e8521a503be88f3757cc43 to ensure
unit tests only run against this repository.

Change-Id: Ie0642cc41c016fc016b2bc6fc6d04b6afdf2be2c

(cherry picked from commit cb435cea4545599bef2ccd8bf053453d6d69cd25)

commit_message:
Add 'openstack-db' tag to db-sync Exec resource

In order to make easy orchestration on all OpenStack db-sync, add this
tag so people can use this tag in composition layer.
A use case it to set some orchestration to make sure MySQL Galera is
ready before running any Exec with this tag.

Change-Id: Ic20686247bc865ee5c8bcc16ac166b193aa071dc
Closes-Bug: #1755102

We will not broke all those projects with this change? Are You sure?'}, {'account_id': 5367, 'date': '2018-03-13 16:11:19.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2:

This is no different than any other neutron-lib consumption change:
- The remaining consumers [1] are not using stable branches. You can verify by looking at each project's requirements.txt and ensuring they are using the latest version of neutron-lib (1.13.0). If they are not using the latest, they are not using stable branches and will need to address the change when they "move up".
- Those using stable branches are already using lib's version [2].


This is how we've been doing neutron-lib consumption patches for awhile now; if we inform the projects of each NeutronLibImpact change
there will be many emails per week. I outlined this approach awhile back [3].


Please do double check that the remaining consumers are not using stable branches [1]. If I missed any please do flag so I can land a patch for them.


Thanks


[1] http://codesearch.openstack.org/?q=from%20neutron.common%20import%20topics&i=nope&files=&repos=
[2] https://review.openstack.org/#/q/topic:use-lib-agenttopics+(status:open+OR+status:merged)
[3] http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack-dev/2017-October/124095.html'}, {'account_id': 5367, 'date': '2018-03-13 17:36:03.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 3.'}, {'account_id': 11975, 'date': '2018-03-13 20:47:09.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 3: Code-Review+2

I checked all those projects once again and none of them uses current neutron-lib so I'm fine with this change now. Thx once again for Your patience and explanation boden :)"}, {'account_id': 4694, 'date': '2018-03-13 21:55:30.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3: Workflow+1 Code-Review+2'}]

commit_message:
use common agent topics from neutron-lib

The neutron.common.topics module was rehomed into neutron-lib with
commit Ie88b84949cbd55a4e7ad06341aab77b286cdc485
This patch consumes it by removing the rehomed module from neutron
and using the module from neutron-lib instead.

NeutronLibImpact

Change-Id: Ia4a4604c259ce862597de80c6deeb3d408bf0e95

commit_message:
Don't double-filter replication jobs

ObjectReplicator.collect_jobs() takes and correctly applies the
various overrides, so there's no need to check the returned jobs
against the overrides.

Change-Id: I2a59b26410d1732a5f2c8f1f32e397d77550860e

commit_message:
[ci] Fix murano job

murano requires heat, so we need to add proper devstack plugin to the
desired job.

PS: manual enabling heat services are redundant, everything should work
    with just enabled plugin

Change-Id: I62febd935b75b4a126d5ce29984f63636463cb3a

commit_message:
Handle SDK changes

stable/queens allows SDK >=0.9.19 and <=0.11.3.  Somewhere in there the
return text of an exception changed.

Backport portions of Id6de1485bcafb41f238f3e74277094ce64a6acf4 to handle
this change, but modify to work with either text form sice both are allowed.

Change-Id: Ibfee8e1e2ae4eca763894bbee8747297e0fb350f

[{'created': '2018-03-13 22:09:43.000000000', 'message': "Parent legacy-gerrit-buck to legacy-base

This currently fails with

  Unable to freeze job graph: Pre-review pipeline check does not allow
  post-review job legacy-gerrit-buck

because the artifacts parent is a protected job, so can't be in the
check pipeline.  I think what's happening here is that this job just
tests the build of the packages, and the -publish variant actually
wants to publish it.

Change-Id: I2111a29e28d091a365e65936ec34a909d8cce980
"}]
commit_message:
Parent legacy-gerrit-buck to legacy-base

This currently fails with

  Unable to freeze job graph: Pre-review pipeline check does not allow
  post-review job legacy-gerrit-buck

because the artifacts parent is a protected job, so can't be in the
check pipeline.  I think what's happening here is that this job just
tests the build of the packages, and the -publish variant actually
wants to publish it.

Change-Id: I2111a29e28d091a365e65936ec34a909d8cce980

'}, {'created': '2018-03-01 08:28:53.000000000', 'message': 'Fix multinode mode for devstack

Extend the devstack job so that it can support both single and multinode
cases.  Multinode mode require extra settings in devstack configuration,
some of which as subnode specific, some controller specific.

Also keep a simple devstack-multinode job defined for now so we can run
a multinode job in devstack gate, until the full tempest multinode job
is ready to match the old
gate-tempest-dsvm-neutron-multinode-full-ubuntu-xenial-nv.

Fixing multinode also requires sharing the CA configuration between
controller and peers, overlay network configuration for communication
between virtual machines and running discover_hosts for nova after the
subnode has been setup.

The extra orchestration required for multinode is encoded in a
dedicated role to allow for jobs in other repos to re-use it.

Depends-on: https://review.openstack.org/548049
Change-Id: I2dcbd9bdb401860820e655d97aa3c4775af2827f

commit_message:
Fix multinode mode for devstack

Extend the devstack job so that it can support both single and multinode
cases.  Multinode mode require extra settings in devstack configuration,
some of which as subnode specific, some controller specific.

Also keep a simple devstack-multinode job defined for now so we can run
a multinode job in devstack gate, until the full tempest multinode job
is ready to match the old
gate-tempest-dsvm-neutron-multinode-full-ubuntu-xenial-nv.

Fixing multinode also requires sharing the CA configuration between
controller and peers, overlay network configuration for communication
between virtual machines and running discover_hosts for nova after the
subnode has been setup.

The extra orchestration required for multinode is encoded in a
dedicated role to allow for jobs in other repos to re-use it.

Change-Id: I2dcbd9bdb401860820e655d97aa3c4775af2827f

3. This would need a release note.
4. Is dns-<lbid> better than the stock host-<ip>?'}, {'account_id': 17776, 'date': '2017-04-05 06:46:15.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 12: Workflow-1

Let me know your thoughts'}, {'account_id': 11628, 'date': '2018-03-13 22:28:38.000000000', 'content': 'Abandoned

The comments on this patch have not been addressed in two years. Abandoning.'}]

commit_message:
Assign dns-name to port during LB creation

Ports created during LoadBalancer creation are
now assigned a dns-name as well if dns-integration
extension is enabled.

Change-Id: I426348b98ae9fe29da874b5ac042074c2bb9b52e
Closes-Bug: #1537169

commit_message:
Use stable-queens build of horizon for stable/queens

This patch changes tox to use the appropriate stable
build of Horizon.

We are currently always pulling the very latest version
of Horizon for all our gates. This is usually fine for the 
first few months, but over time it's likely that Horizon 
introduces changes that will break the designate-dashboard tests
and block the gate.

Change-Id: I077823a21073827c66b0bf0359909438435faeda
Closes-Bug: #1754269

Add tests for APTRepositoryCacheUpdateRule

The custom ansible-lint rule APTRepositoryCacheUpdateRule was added in
67bfc907030d7f0ce6fbb63f0608aa021f0b5400, this change adds tests to
validate its functionality.

Includes fix from 44761d390b9f9f4794e8521a503be88f3757cc43 to ensure
unit tests only run against this repository.

Change-Id: Ie0642cc41c016fc016b2bc6fc6d04b6afdf2be2c
Partial-bug: 1750656
(cherry picked from commit cb435cea4545599bef2ccd8bf053453d6d69cd25)

commit_message:
Re-work the metadata service docs

The metadata service docs were hard to find since they were nested
down in some nova-network admin guide docs, and they were a mix of
end user and admin deployment guide information.

This change splits out the end-user facing content into a user
guide and leaves the deployment-specific information in the admin
guide, and links are updated appropriately.

The admin guide portion also referenced some config options that no
longer exist, so those are also removed and vendordata_providers
is added with a link to the vendordata guide. The options themselves
are cleaned up for their current groups and linked to the config option
docs.

Change-Id: I66035366f3a7ca62ea12d6afa74d13db01ec9f8d

commit_message:
Log config options with oslo.config

This removes some custom code inherited from Cinder which was handling
the output of secret options in a bad way. This patch utilizes Oslo's
existing utilities to output the Manila configuration options securely.

Filtering will be done with the "secret=True" option flag.

Major thanks to Eric Harney for introducing this fix to Cinder.

Change-Id: I894e011680661c0b73b9592f70a6457e403f18c6
Related-Bug: #1750074

commit_message:
[upstream] Fixes url and uses https as possible

- Fixes corrupted links
 : In Stackalytics, integrated -> official
   (Previously, projects were categorized as integrated, experimental, ...)
 : https://www.openstack.org/blog/ urls now use numbers
   instead of title names
 : Jenkins -> Zuul (Infra documents were already changed)
 : Fixed on upstream institutes registration in opnfv-2017
- Uses https as much as possible

Change-Id: I6a5fea0e93c85ada6bf0d07ca1fabe94646e1b98

commit_message:
Switch subnet-pool id for name

This commit switches subnet-pool id for name on the create subnet
funcion on our devstack plugin as it's currently broken because of the
migration in between q-* and neutron-* services in devstack.

This intends to be a temporary measure until we get our dependencies
sorted out.

Change-Id: Ibaf0eaf9b1dcacebf2c38e81cbd7f6136ade556b

commit_message:
Panko api wsgi changed path for Ubuntu

When installing the panko-api and panko-common
packages for Ubuntu the path to the wsgi script is
no longer /usr/share/panko-common/app.wsgi but is
now /usr/lib/python2.7/dist-packages/panko/api/app.wsgi

This patch changes that script path. It depends on the
Gnocchi change in order to test this since Gnocchi has
to be fixed in order to run testing. [1]

[1] https://review.openstack.org/#/c/548032/

Depends-On: I070f88dd40ca4129cbd3abf5b4f5ecb511b2895e
Change-Id: I066bd87ce839d380942adcb73fcaa6d915f801c1
(cherry picked from commit 4a890fc2f1f61505b74aa52a3c75e6791800e574)

commit_message:
Use rest_status_code for api-ref response codes

Rather than our freeform way of listing response codes in our
api-ref, we should be using the os-api-ref extension option to
get nicely formatted response code listings.

https://docs.openstack.org/os-api-ref/latest/usage.html#rest-status-code

Change-Id: Iee21f54fe7cf0ea28258966e2d0f8fa2849c83f2

commit_message:
Re-implement novaclient bits removed in 10.0

a)

/os-floating-ips was removed in Compute API 2.36 and from novaclient's
Python API in 10.0

Add to api.computev2:
floating_ip_add()
floating_ip_remove()

Convert add floating IP command to nova-net/neutron split:
"server add floating ip"
"server remove floating ip"

b)

/os-hosts was removed in Compute API 2.43 and from novaclient's
Python API in 10.0.

Add to api.computev2:
host_list()
host_set()
host_show()

Convert host commands to use intenal api:
"host list"
"host set"
"host show"

c)

The introduction of the Network-style commands into the server group
broke cliff's autoprogram directive as it executes the get_parser() methods
without fully initializing the Command object.

NOTE: This is really three reviews squashed to get through the gate in one pass.

Depends-on: Id6de87211d6c4ea8fd14aa9203d8d5b17e9e2f04
Change-Id: I5116086f9a9e4b2b31a744bf8f4558c79f0bfe59

While generally supported by iPXE, in DevStack we do not have any
facilities in place to boot iPXE from a HTTPS URL when the server is
using a custom certificate.
This is moslty concerning ability to boot iPXE directly from Swift's
TempURL when SSL is enabled on Swift in DevStack.

Just die with proper message when IRONIC_IPXE_USE_SWIFT and tls-proxy

"}]
commit_message:
[devstack] block iPXE boot from HTTPS TempURLs

While generally supported by iPXE, in DevStack we do not have any
facilities in place to boot iPXE from a HTTPS URL when the server is
using a custom certificate.
This is moslty concerning ability to boot iPXE directly from Swift's
TempURL when SSL is enabled on Swift in DevStack.

Just die with proper message when IRONIC_IPXE_USE_SWIFT and tls-proxy
are both enabled.

Change-Id: Ie0e01828f05b2706d310d8110e6e8dd8c4a03e4e

I see no change to test_objects for the version fingerprinting. I assume that means either (a) you're not really changing the namespacing here, or (b) you orphaned a bunch of cruft in the fingerprint map and now aren't testing that they're the same?

If the former, then I'm not sure I see the point here, and if the latter, I'd like to see that. I want to see that none of the objects have changed as a part of this move and so I want to make sure the fingerprints are unchanged and still being checked.

That said, this is really large and I think it can/should be split up into at least a few pieces.

Moving the field definitions out to a common place, and all the related virt driver (etc) changes can be one.

Moving the resource_providers module into placement can be another change. Just a straight move so we can tell that nothing functional has changed. Ideally with a separate fingerprint change that has the same hashes but moved to a different place.

Reparenting the objects can be another change, hopefully with clear lack of change in fingerprints, or some way to tell what has changed so we can write it off as unrelated.

Also, I do think it's *really* weird to have the objects under the api hierarchy as Matt pointed out. I'm not sure I really see the value in this shuffle to begin with, but if we're going to do it, I think we shouldn't just be shoving things under api because that's where the rest of placement stuff is."}, {'account_id': 11564, 'date': '2018-03-08 16:41:39.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 11:

revisions:
[{'created': '2018-02-01 17:38:20.000000000', 'message': 'WIP: Move resource provider objects into placement hierarchy

This is so we don't have all the other objects imported into the
the placement process, which happens by virtue of being in the
nova.objects package. It also eases the eventual extraction of
placement.

In the process make some adjustments to minimize the amount of
"nova" in the objects that placement uses:

* Make the resource provider objects inherit from oslo_versionedobjects,
  not nova objects.
* Move the ResourceClass field to its own package, and move that package
  to the top of the nova hierarchy since it is used by both nova tooling
  and placement tooling but we don't want the placement version to have
  to incorporate the nova code.

This latter change is the source of most of the changes, as
standard ResourceClass fields are used all over the place and we need
to distinguish between other fields and the resource class fields.
I considered providing a sort of proxy class, but being explicit seemed
better.

Change-Id: Iea182341f9419cb514a044f76864d6bec60a3683

commit_message:
Move resource class fields

Move the ResourceClass field to its own package, and move that package
to the top of the nova hierarchy since it is used by both nova tooling
and placement tooling but we don't want the placement version to have to
incorporate the nova code. Eventually we'd like to see an
os-resource-classes library, similar to os-traits, which will serve this
functionality. This is a step in that direction.

Changes in this patch are quite widespread, but are mostly only changes
of imports.

Change-Id: Iea182341f9419cb514a044f76864d6bec60a3683

commit_message:
kernel: make ExtraKernelModules and ExtraSysctlSettings role-specific

Allow to configure extra Kernel modules and extra sysctl settings per role
and not only global to the whole deployment.
The two parameters that can be role-specific are ExtraKernelModules and
ExtraSysctlSettings.

Depends-On: I2b26ce4f9d19dbf66da1b4382d7ffd653e67a92e
Change-Id: Iaafd0133df7ecd01a338f1b4deb3b159c2d9c6f1
(cherry picked from commit da1ed3d19c54b5f60fdc883fd4f11f613914c854)

commit_message:
Don't double load config

This isn't necessary and will likely have some bad side effects
because re-calling the conf object clears all previously registered
opts, which defeats the purpose of the second call.

Change-Id: I59bd78e85b3d55aea23b46809f4de678d394f66d
Related-Bug: 1751815

commit_message:
Adding the class and mac approach as dpdk-devargs in mellanox ConnectX-3

Some NICs (i.e. Mellanox ConnectX-3) have only one PCI address
associated with multiple ports. Using a PCI address as dpdk-devargs
in OvsDpdkPort won't work. Instead, class and mac approach is used
dpdk-devargs="class=eth,mac=<MAC>"
see this http://docs.openvswitch.org/en/latest/howto/dpdk/

Closes-Bug: #1754256
Change-Id: I29de6e82a0897ee46953a1e6a966e9c5790068c9
(cherry picked from commit aeaa6fe62b39a00f3b075a94c076f267f0c70af0)

commit_message:
Adding a workaround for enabling steering in ConnectX-3 devices

This file will add this configuration
"options mlx4_core log_num_mgm_entry_size=-1" to
/etc/modprobe.d/mlx4.conf file in order to enable steering in
ConnectX-3 devices and then will rebuild the initramfs at the first
boot stage

Closes-Bug: #1754260
Change-Id: Ia64e62e7fdb70e19be7b0a5cee163bd03c6de65d
(cherry picked from commit bbc8e0ac3e37752b4f114811878cabd544746923)

commit_message:

If validations are enabled, set EnableValidations to true.
It'll allow containerized undercloud to run workbooks usually executed
by instack-undercloud, in
THT/extraconfig/post_deploy/undercloud_post.sh.

Change-Id: I10abed7f1514e9d72d5ebac0c85bad11cdf3210f

[{'created': '2018-03-13 13:43:16.000000000', 'message': "Flush console log file before retrieving content

Hyper-V exposes instance serial console ports through named pipes.
We're consuming those named pipes, logging the output to a file,
retrieving the content when the console output is requested.

The issue is that the log file used by os-win never gets flushed
(unless closed). For this reason, we're returning incomplete output.

Closes-Bug: #1741494

Change-Id: Ic558b16b317e0b1478cc259327d1336f7589afe3

commit_message:
Flush console log file before retrieving content

Hyper-V exposes instance serial console ports through named pipes.
We're consuming those named pipes, logging the output to a file,
retrieving the content when the console output is requested.

The issue is that the log file used by os-win never gets flushed
(unless closed). For this reason, we're returning incomplete output.

This change ensures that we're flushing the log file before attempting
to read its content.

commit_message:
Use stable-pike build of horizon for stable/pike

This patch changes tox to use the appropriate stable
build of Horizon.

We are currently always pulling the very latest version
of Horizon for all our gates. This is usually fine for the 
first few months, but over time it's likely that Horizon 
introduces changes that will break the designate-dashboard tests
and block the gate.

Change-Id: I3cecd9e1adce7ef0748f181050ed5d7cbe0da317
Closes-Bug: #1754269

commit_message:
Add custom action to add dns entries via novajoin

When TLS is setup using novajoin, the IdM server should be
used for DNS.  This patch provides custom actions/workflow to
create the required entries through a call to novajoin.

This patch partially resolves BZ 1534070.

commit_message:
WIP: Add DNS data to IdM

When TLS is set up using novajoin and IdM, the IdM server should
be used for DNS.  This patch provides DNS data to novajoin so that
it can add it to IdM in two ways.
* by adding VipDnsData to the instance metadata to be processed on
  server instantiation.
* by calling a custom action to add entries when the deployment
  is complete

Change-Id: Ia8a282a2f8c2a6941c4e8735c797b01fd3790a63
Depends-On: I6bd2dd42e57cf84dadce6476317d3a118bf14110

commit_message:
[CVE-2018-1000115] memcached: restrict to TCP & localhost

https://access.redhat.com/security/cve/cve-2018-1000115

Restrict Memcached to only work on TCP and localhost.
The restriction is made at the application and firewall levels.
It will prevent DDoS amplification attacks using memcached.

Change-Id: I8072cc842291d133fde9fdfe9e8ad432623a8ef2
Related-Bug: #1754607

commit_message:
Add ansible-lint rule for apt_repository

This rule is designed to prevent the Ansible module `apt_repository`
from being used to update the APT cache. There is a bug [1] in
`apt_repository` that prevents cache updates from being performed
whenever the module is retried. If the cache update fails at the first
attempt, it is skipped on the subsequent attempt of the task causing the
task to always complete successfully. Until this bug is addressed this
rule should prevent it from being introduced into OpenStack-Ansible.

Partial-bug: 1750656

[1] https://github.com/ansible/ansible/issues/36605

Change-Id: If440ce129c31fb4e62a8e0ac5094195f4d4d7167
(cherry picked from commit 67bfc907030d7f0ce6fbb63f0608aa021f0b5400)

[{'created': '2018-03-07 15:29:54.000000000', 'message': "Add deploy_status to plan-environment

Now that we support deploying via --config-download, it's no longer
possible for e.g the UI to monitor the status of the plan deployment
via the heat stack status, so add a status key to the plan-environment.

This can be used to check the status of the plan deployment after the
plan create/update/delete has finished (e.g there's no status on the
zaqar queue to consume).

The mistral workflows that manage the plan lifecycle will update the
value as appropriate, e.g:

CREATED - plan validated and created in swift
DEPLOYING - deployment is in-progress (either heat or configuration)
ERROR - deployment failed with some error
DELETED - plan still exists but the deployment has been deleted

We could consider splitting DEPLOYING perhaps to differentiate
the heat stack (PROVISIONING?) phase with the ansible/config-download
phase (CONFIGURING?)

"}]
commit_message:
Add deploy_status to plan-environment

Now that we support deploying via --config-download, it's no longer
possible for e.g the UI to monitor the status of the plan deployment
via the heat stack status, so add a status key to the plan-environment.

This can be used to check the status of the plan deployment after the
plan create/update/delete has finished (e.g there's no status on the
zaqar queue to consume).

The mistral workflows that manage the plan lifecycle will update the
value as appropriate, e.g:

CREATED - plan validated and created in swift
DEPLOYING - deployment is in-progress (either heat or configuration)
ERROR - deployment failed with some error
DELETED - plan still exists but the deployment has been deleted

We could consider splitting DEPLOYING perhaps to differentiate
the heat stack (PROVISIONING?) phase with the ansible/config-download
phase (CONFIGURING?)

Change-Id: I9a08bcd45be082b0050cb77ca9587520da5f8280

commit_message:
Mock retry in test_remove_block_dev

test_remove_block_dev was a very long running test. It was not mocking
retrying.retry and the retries would continue until the retry timeout
was hit. This adds test_remove_block_dev_timeout which mocks retry
while verifying the RetryError device deletion failure case to reduce
the test runtime.

Change-Id: I8cf674cb48d672bde3ce44660bc619aa4c914e62

commit_message:
Support disabling a cell

It would be useful to have a mechanism by which we could totally stop
scheduling to a particular cell or a group of cells by supporting the
concept of disabling cells. Given that we do not have any existing
means to disable a cell, this spec proposes a simple solution to
support this new feature in nova.

Change-Id: I22bfe4dbe8325e57cef9959c38adda94fef28d73
Implements: blueprint cell-disable

commit_message:
use defusedxml to avoid XML attack

According to https://docs.openstack.org/bandit/latest/api/bandit.blacklists.html

Using various XML methods to parse untrusted XML data is known to be vulnerable
to XML attacks. Methods should be replaced with their defusedxml equivalents.

Change-Id: Icdd807c8fd47ce0df3e292eef910e6e6e7610686
Partial-Bug: #1732155

commit_message:
crypto: Remove unused functions

These top-level functions were not called from anywhere but tests.

- fetch_ca
- ensure_ca_filesystem
- fetch_crl
- decrypt_text
- revoke_certs_by_user
- revoke_certs_by_project
- revoke_certs_by_user_and_project
- generate_x509_cert
- generate_vpn_files

These other functions are used by the above and are no longer used
anywhere.

- ca_folder
- ca_path
- key_path
- crl_path
- revoke_cert
- _project_cert_subject
- _user_cert_subject
- _ensure_project_folder
- sign_csr
- _sign_csr

Tests for these are removed as are a number of scripts found in
'nova/CA', which were only used by the aforementioned functions.

Change-Id: Ie1dadc6bf935f777e0cd0c54a0a21b79545714c5

commit_message:
Allow for merging traits and aggregates

Per discussions at the PTG [1] as concluded in IRC [2][3][4],
update_provider_tree needs to set and unset only the traits and
aggregate associations it "owns", rather than replacing them wholesale.
To facilitate this, we're adding ProviderTree methods add_traits,
remove_traits, add_aggregates, and remove_aggregates.

[1] Awkwardly pasted, since no etherpad permalink: http://paste.openstack.org/raw/698758/
[2] http://eavesdrop.openstack.org/meetings/nova_scheduler/2018/nova_scheduler.2018-03-12-14.00.log.html#l-217
[3] http://eavesdrop.openstack.org/irclogs/%23openstack-nova/%23openstack-nova.2018-03-12.log.html#t2018-03-12T16:08:09
[4] http://eavesdrop.openstack.org/irclogs/%23openstack-nova/%23openstack-nova.2018-03-12.log.html#t2018-03-12T18:29:56

commit_message:
[CVE-2018-1000115] memcached: restrict to TCP & localhost

https://access.redhat.com/security/cve/cve-2018-1000115

Restrict Memcached to only work on TCP and localhost.
The restriction is made at the application and firewall levels.
It will prevent DDoS amplification attacks using memcached.

Change-Id: I8072cc842291d133fde9fdfe9e8ad432623a8ef2
Related-Bug: #1754607
(cherry picked from commit 74fc85c507fc298828797c51255cee059a9684fc)

commit_message:
Updating time for functional tests

Currenlty, some gates is being failed with logs like this

"""
b'Response: {"description": "Provided object does not match schema
\'Secret\': \'expiration\' is before current time.
Invalid property: \'expiration\'", "title": "Bad Request", "code": 400}'
"""

So it is necessary to update the time to create secrets successfully.

Change-Id: I59707cdf21f6843dbd7db30978e21cff72756e67

commit_message:
Fix for difference in tzinfo.tzname value between py27 and py35

The tzinfo.tzname value differs between py27 and py35.
For example, 'UTC' for py27, 'UTC+00:00' for py35.
Therefore, it is necessary to change the way to get the date string.

Change-Id: Iae5539e0aec0fab0a08640f7f6600a1d91b241e5
Closes-Bug: #1753644

commit_message:
base: use ERP:kolla:queens repo for Debian

At Linaro we try to keep repositories with extra packages as separate as
it is possible. ERP:kolla is used for 'master' builds and we had
'ERP:kolla:pike' in past.

So I created 'ERP:kolla:queens' repo for stable/queens builds.

Change-Id: I6de4e1d1bf214f364b907ab85a0d0eeb233b4952

commit_message:
Update for upcoming openstacksdk changes to masakari-monitors

In the next openstacksdk release, Profile is going away as are entrypoints
plugins. This handles fixing most of that in a way that should work with
both old and new.

Note: This code has been tested with a version other than
openstacksdk-0.10.0.

Change-Id: Ic6390b0a479529600d246e3ced9e7278f08054df

commit_message:
Use node traits during upgrade

Now that the queens branch has support for node traits in the devstack
plugin [1], we can apply node traits when testing upgrades from queens
or later.

[1] https://review.openstack.org/551938

Change-Id: I99b9487d849ecd5241657d6ca91c2e9f9f7dfcf8
Related-Bug: #1722194
Related-Bug: #1750027

commit_message:
Remove default value for Cinder Auth Strategy

Cinder supports both noauth and keystone auth mode. So now we can
configure this value via local.conf:

[[post-config|$CINDER_CONF]]
[DEFAULT]
auth_strategy = noauth

Change-Id: I1e434362117ab30dae71a8f3a80bc139e78f51bc

So change the test template allowed_pattern.

commit_message:
Allow to configure max vlans for trunk port tests

In NFV baremetal deployments, the number of vlans available for trunk
ports may be constrained. This patch allows to configure
max_networks_per_project to accommodate for those environments.

Change-Id: Ie0f04649313aed41498cf60f7de0eb44cee17b1c

commit_message:
Remove customizable for plugins_pip_packages

The pip packages are normally already configurable with the
<image_name>_pip_packages variable. It doesn't make much sense to make
the list of packages installed with the plugins mechanism configurable
via the <image_name>_plugins_pip_packages variable too.

And even if we wanted to, the parameter to the `customizable()`
function should be 'plugins_pip_packages' and not 'pip_packages'.

This commit removes the customizable bits from the plugins install
macro, at least until we get a good use case for it.

Change-Id: I90dd28b8c5d981e6028af353e34645712ef09b0b

commit_message:
Support configuration of Kafka package

This change makes it easier to configure the Kafka package. This
is useful, for example, when installing Monasca which currently
requires an older version of Kafka than that installed here.

The change also fixes an issue with circular symlinks, updates
kafka and verifies the sha512sum of the package. The sha512sum
was taken from here:

https://www.apache.org/dist/kafka/1.0.1/kafka_2.12-1.0.1.tgz.sha512

Change-Id: I79a5a32ee8e5edd915fa88fbc00d0d4ac08b8ebd
Partially-Implements: blueprint monasca-roles

subject: Move gnocchi api in wsgi back to python2
messages: [{'account_id': 16137, 'date': '2018-03-11 09:19:40.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Cherry Picked from branch master.'}, {'account_id': 16137, 'date': '2018-03-11 09:36:14.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 2.'}, {'account_id': 16137, 'date': '2018-03-12 08:12:49.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 3.'}, {'account_id': 16137, 'date': '2018-03-12 11:55:19.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 4.'}, {'account_id': 3153, 'date': '2018-03-12 13:18:59.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 4: Code-Review+2'}, {'account_id': 1004, 'date': '2018-03-13 13:16:23.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 4: Workflow+1 Code-Review+2'}]
revisions:
[{'created': '2018-03-11 09:19:40.000000000', 'message': 'Move gnocchi api in wsgi back to python2

Canonical are packaging gnocchi-api package with apache
and python3 by default. We cannot test it in CI since
we cannot run py2 and py3 on the same node with apache wsgi.

Canonical helped us by packaging python2 support back into
python-gnocchi package so we change our wsgi usage to use
this package and set the new wsgi script path.

We still want users to be able to install only gnocchi-api
since they might not run apache wsgi even though its installed by
default.

Adds installation of rados and redis packages for python3
when needed, this is because all gnocchi components will
still be running in py3, also CLI such as gnocchi-upgrade
but the gnocchi-api is in wsgi using py2. Because of that
we still need to install the py2 packages.

Enables acceptance testing for Debian based operating systems.

Change-Id: I070f88dd40ca4129cbd3abf5b4f5ecb511b2895e
(cherry picked from commit 56794f300acaf0c2dd46a0bac3830f7c90120670)

Change-Id: I070f88dd40ca4129cbd3abf5b4f5ecb511b2895e

'}]
commit_message:
Move gnocchi api in wsgi back to python2

Canonical are packaging gnocchi-api package with apache
and python3 by default. We cannot test it in CI since
we cannot run py2 and py3 on the same node with apache wsgi.

Canonical helped us by packaging python2 support back into
python-gnocchi package so we change our wsgi usage to use
this package and set the new wsgi script path.

We still want users to be able to install only gnocchi-api
since they might not run apache wsgi even though its installed by
default.

Adds installation of rados and redis packages for python3
when needed, this is because all gnocchi components will
still be running in py3, also CLI such as gnocchi-upgrade
but the gnocchi-api is in wsgi using py2. Because of that
we still need to install the py2 packages.

Enables acceptance testing for Debian based operating systems.

Change-Id: I070f88dd40ca4129cbd3abf5b4f5ecb511b2895e
(cherry picked from commit 56794f300acaf0c2dd46a0bac3830f7c90120670)

commit_message:
Define devstack services without the test-matrix

Emit a disable_all_services and define which service we run in
the job directly. This drops the dependency from the test matrix,
from devstack default list of services and it makes it easier for
jobs to add/remove services based on the list in the base job.

Change-Id: Ib1debefd541b933dbfc54d484c263cc0ed60423d

commit_message:
Reduce stestr concurrency to 1 for tempest jobs

The switch from testr to stestr introduced in Change-Id
Icf1f9eb4539666dffb6c9c1651670541523a9f9e missed setting concurrency
jobs to 1 for api and scenario tests, leading to intermittent gate
issues.

This patch also fixes coverage test that got broken in the
aforementioned Change-Id.

Change-Id: I052a9c3b376624f8e9e63faa98f4d09a93bdde4d

commit_message:
Add nfs as a cinder backup driver option to CinderBackupBackend

Added nfs as an option to where CinderBackupBackend was hardcoded
as either ceph or swift. Also added some parameters for this
driver - CinderBackupNfsShare and CinderBackupNfsMountOptions

Change-Id: Id155e59703bf8b14da33ae54482b9d3bfcc4115e
Closes-Bug: #1744174

commit_message:
Pass user context to virt driver when detaching volume

We need this in a later change to pull volume attachment
information from cinder for the volume being detached so
that we can do some attachment counting for multiattach
volumes being detached from instances on the same host.

(cherry-picked from commit d2941bfd165055348dd584b630d4e631ef05e328)

Change-Id: If6e869b1c3516220b7deb0599d699caa2ed33889
Related-Bug: #1752115
(cherry picked from commit e27b94287739207640b37ffd3e3a6b4176ef7cd3)

(2 comments)

commit_message:
Virtual instance rescue with stable disk devices

This will provide the ability to indicate that the rescue disk image
should be attached as a transient disk device (ie USB stick), so that
existing storage attached to an instance doesn't change its device
address during rescue mode.

This version of the spec for Queens additionally describes changes to
the REST API requested during Newton.

Previously-approved: Mitaka, Newton

Change-Id: I6f9a7aa7e5306988230ae4c19045efc70c582244
Blueprint: virt-rescue-stable-disk-devices

commit_message:
Update config option for collecting sensor data

This patch updates the notification driver option for collecting sensor
data because [DEFAULT]/notification_driver is deprecated and
'messaging' driver should only be used in cases where there are existing
consumers deployed which do not support the 2.0 message format.

Change-Id: Ia6c55149e5cb12d1201742f7008047e35570b410

This patch makes it possible to build the Virtualbox-compatible OVA
archive withouth using vagrant, virtualbox, or vmware-specific tools.

Currently the created ova archive can be imported on VirtualBox and
VMWare Player, the disk image itself can be used with libvirt
(qemu-kvm). It contains all the drivers that enables using it
as a desktop system with shared clipboard, auto-resizing display, etc.

Since the diskimage-builder method installs in chroot, there is no way
to pre-install devstack by running stack.sh. The image makes a best
effort including all the deb and pip packages to make the first run of
stack.sh as short as possible.

commit_message:
Moving to diskimage-builder

This patch makes it possible to build the Virtualbox-compatible OVA
archive withouth using vagrant, virtualbox, or vmware-specific tools.

Currently the created ova archive can be imported on VirtualBox and
VMWare Player, the disk image itself can be used with libvirt
(qemu-kvm). It contains all the drivers that enables using it
as a desktop system with shared clipboard, auto-resizing display, etc.

Since the diskimage-builder method installs in chroot, there is no way
to pre-install devstack by running stack.sh. The image makes a best
effort including all the deb and pip packages to make the first run of
stack.sh as short as possible.

Change-Id: Ie1f6e44db7e0af8d072cfdf16ace1ba3f749c246

commit_message:
[CVE-2018-1000115] memcached: restrict to TCP & localhost

https://access.redhat.com/security/cve/cve-2018-1000115

Restrict Memcached to only work on TCP and localhost.
The restriction is made at the application and firewall levels.
It will prevent DDoS amplification attacks using memcached.

commit_message:
[CVE-2018-1000115] memcached: restrict to TCP & localhost

https://access.redhat.com/security/cve/cve-2018-1000115

Restrict Memcached to only work on TCP and localhost.
The restriction is made at the application and firewall levels.
It will prevent DDoS amplification attacks using memcached.

Change-Id: I8072cc842291d133fde9fdfe9e8ad432623a8ef2
Related-Bug: #1754607
(cherry picked from commit 74fc85c507fc298828797c51255cee059a9684fc)

commit_message:
Implements validate_rescue() for IRMCVirtualMediaBoot

This commit implements validate_rescue() for 'irmc-virtual-media'
boot interface of 'irmc' hardware type.

With this it enables 'agent' rescue interface for 'irmc' hardware
type when corresponding boot interface being used is
'irmc-virtual-media'. Support already exists for the 'agent'
rescue interface with 'irmc-pxe' boot interface.

Also fix a bug in _remove_share_file() causing files
not to be removed correctly.

Change-Id: Ib602b2705b8fa4f7161b9f97857ec6546f5e9b19
Closes-Bug: #1747842

commit_message:
Add LXC swap metric collector and fix lxc bug

LXC plugin throw up a exception when try collect cpu metrics. This
patch fix it (tests are passing) and add swap collector.

Change-Id: I3b12ac6ce199006bc1e024d2b2626657519e4f0b
Story: 2001563
Task: 6507

commit_message:
Fix telegraf output for influxdb

Kolla add multiple url in one outputs.influxdb.
This configuration is when influxdb is in cluster mode.
We need to write one conf by influxdb server.

Change-Id: I1c788b3c8400e74d50cace5a334311408989c5e1

commit_message:
Pass user context to virt driver when detaching volume

We need this in a later change to pull volume attachment
information from cinder for the volume being detached so
that we can do some attachment counting for multiattach
volumes being detached from instances on the same host.

(cherry-picked from commit d2941bfd165055348dd584b630d4e631ef05e328)

Change-Id: If6e869b1c3516220b7deb0599d699caa2ed33889
Related-Bug: #1752115

commit_message:
Flush console log file before retrieving content

Hyper-V exposes instance serial console ports through named pipes.
We're consuming those named pipes, logging the output to a file,
retrieving the content when the console output is requested.

The issue is that the log file used by os-win never gets flushed
(unless closed). For this reason, we're returning incomplete output.

This change ensures that we're flushing the log file before attempting
to read its content.

Closes-Bug: #1741494

Change-Id: Ic558b16b317e0b1478cc259327d1336f7589afe3
Depends-On: I4b5eb7579ac0c92e9c3630539b0c4d76f5b98c6d

use is_extension_supported from neutron-lib

The is_extension_supported function now lives in neutron-lib. This patch
removes the function from neutron and uses lib's version instead.

NeutronLibImpact

Change-Id: Iccb72e00f85043b3dff0299df7eb1279655e313e

revisions:
[{'created': '2017-05-31 19:08:19.000000000', 'message': "Improve endpoint_type handling

since [0] DevStack has simplified its keystone catalog by only
registering public endpoints for services, but ironic defaults to
'internal' API endpoints when discovering those from keystone catalog.

Although ironic was not broken yet due to explicitly setting the API urls
for various services in our config, we should move to discovery from
catalog eventually.
To support this, add 'endpoint_type' config options
for those services that might already use it (currently neutron and
service_catalog config sections, but others will follow).

Also, follow suit with DevStack by registering only a public ironic API
endpoint in our devstack plugin.

[0] https://review.openstack.org/#/c/433272

Change-Id: I1283ef3b4d736ac089df0cc74a5850a93b24b6ab
"}, {'created': '2017-06-06 14:04:47.000000000', 'message': "Improve endpoint_type handling

since [0] DevStack has simplified its keystone catalog by only
registering public endpoints for services, but ironic defaults to
'internal' API endpoints when discovering those from keystone catalog.

Although ironic was not broken yet due to explicitly setting the API urls
for various services in our config, we should move to discovery from
catalog eventually.
To support this, register keystoneauth1.adapter.Adapter options to all
config sections for service clients auth.
Among others it exports 'interface' option, that can be set to 'public'
(default in keystoneauth1 and clients) or 'internal'.

Those service clients that need that right away have been changed to used it
(neutron and service_catalog).
Some options in those config sections have been deprecated as well,
as was [keystone]region_name option (and effectively the whole
[keystone] config section).

Also, follow suit with DevStack by registering only a public ironic API
endpoint in our devstack plugin.

"}, {'created': '2017-06-07 10:22:38.000000000', 'message': "Improve endpoint interface handling

since [0] DevStack has simplified its keystone catalog by only
registering public endpoints for services, but ironic defaults to
'internal' API endpoints when discovering those from keystone catalog.

Although ironic was not broken yet due to explicitly or implicitly setting
the API urls for all services in our config, we should move to discovery from
catalog eventually.

To support this, register keystoneauth1.adapter.Adapter options to all
config sections for service clients auth.
Among others it exports `interface` option, that can be set to 'public'
(default in keystoneauth1 and clients) or 'internal'.
Other exported options are `service_type`, `service_name`, `region_name`
and `endpoint_override`.
The latter will eventually be used by all clients to specify a specific
endpoint to use (for example in noauth mode).

Effectively this patch starts to move all clients code to load client
configuration from config for all of auth, session and adapter.

Those service clients that need that right away have been changed to used it
(neutron and service_catalog).
Some options in those config sections have been deprecated as well
(those which are covered by session and adapter options)
as was [keystone]region_name option (and effectively the whole
[keystone] config section).

Also, follow suit with DevStack by registering only a public ironic API
endpoint in our devstack plugin.

[0] https://review.openstack.org/#/c/433272

Change-Id: I1283ef3b4d736ac089df0cc74a5850a93b24b6ab

the API urls for all services in our config, we should move to discovery from
catalog eventually.

To support this, register keystoneauth1.adapter.Adapter options to all
config sections for service clients auth.
Among others it exports `interface` option, that can be set to 'public'
(default in keystoneauth1 and clients) or 'internal'.
Other exported options are `service_type`, `service_name`, `region_name`
and `endpoint_override`.
The latter will eventually be used by all clients to specify a specific
endpoint to use (for example in noauth mode).

Effectively this patch starts to move all clients code to load client
configuration from config for all of auth, session and adapter.
The first to move is [service_catalog] section, with [conductor]api_url
option being deprecated in favor of [service_catalog]endpoint_override.
More patches moving other clients to consume these new options and
deprecate some other options will follow.

Also, follow suit with DevStack by registering only a public ironic API
endpoint in our devstack plugin.

commit_message:
Introduce keystoneauth adapters for clients

Currently ironic explicitly or implicitly sets the API urls
for most services in the config.
This is quite fragile and we should move to discovery from
the keystone catalog eventually.

To support this, this patch registers `keystoneauth1.adapter.Adapter`
options to all config sections for service clients auth.
Among others it exports `interfaces` option that we set to
['internal', 'public'] by default.
Other exported options are `service_type`, `service_name`, `region_name`
and `endpoint_override`.
The latter will eventually be used by all clients to specify a specific
endpoint to use (for example in noauth mode).

Effectively this patch starts to move all clients code to load client
configuration from config for all of auth, session and adapter.

The first to move is [service_catalog] section, with [conductor]api_url
option being deprecated in favor of [service_catalog]endpoint_override.
A sane default of 'service_type' = 'baremetal' is set for this config
section as well.

More patches moving other clients to consume these new options and
deprecate some other options will follow.

Change-Id: I1283ef3b4d736ac089df0cc74a5850a93b24b6ab
Partial-Bug: #1699547
Related-Bug: #1699542

commit_message:
Add reno for RBAC and client incompatibility

Magnumclients older than 2.9.0 (<=2.80) can not create
certificates for RBAC enabled clients. Affects only
k8s_fedora_atomic. This patch adds the relevant reno.

Change-Id: Idab265a41b1bf2da83d29eb942b9f4568ee4cf99

tighten up test for acceptor being same as

Magnumclients older than 2.9.0 (<=2.80) can not create
certificates for RBAC enabled clients. Affects only

Change-Id: Idab265a41b1bf2da83d29eb942b9f4568ee4cf99
'}]
commit_message:
Add reno for RBAC and client incompatibility

Magnumclients older than 2.9.0 (<=2.80) can not create
certificates for RBAC enabled clients. Affects only
k8s_fedora_atomic. This patch adds the relevant reno.

Change-Id: Idab265a41b1bf2da83d29eb942b9f4568ee4cf99

commit_message:
Zuul: Remove project name

Zuul no longer requires the project-name for in-repo configuration.
Omitting it makes forking or renaming projects easier.

Change-Id: Ib4aa233c76512e8e0d3dc3dd519160114f9bfa25

commit_message:
Add file type check to upload-swift-artifacts

deploy-artifacts supports only 'RPM' and 'gzip compressed data' [1]
while upload-swift-artifacts will allow the uploading
of any file. deploy-artifacts will fail if an unsupported file
type is downloaded resutling in a stack deploy failure.

This update add a check_file function which will validate the
file type of each file before it is uploaded. The script will
exit with a failure if an unsupported file is attempted.

Change-Id: I8c46110fa2779b818bc5b7882788f5d8739c1d2a
1: https://github.com/openstack/tripleo-heat-templates/blob/master/puppet/deploy-artifacts.sh#L12-L23

commit_message:
Pin puppet-systemd

puppet-systemd recently added a breaking change to pull the module
parameter defaults via hiera. This only works in puppet >= 4.10.0 which
we are not using. So we need to pin to an earlier commit since we're
usign 4.8.x.

Change-Id: I11c8372eb20d9ff67bcc91897118061d7f193a54
Closes-Bug: #1755211
(cherry picked from commit bd5599ca59b168ce4785991c4165fa4196b8d78a)

Added t-h-t for tempest container

It adds a fake tempest service in order to make tempest
container available on undercloud.

commit_message:
Add prefixlen to subnet api-ref for create actions

Prefixlen is used in subnet creation when allocating a subnet
from a subnet pool.

Change-Id: I251944ca15434ed9b17deb829cca985cd94a0bd1
Closes-bug: #1754062

I'm going to propose we move forward with this patch.
Today the only networking related consumer [1] is networking-vsphere. 
I've had a patch for review in the networking-vsphere queue [2] since mid Jan 2018, and haven't gotten a single review from a networking-vpshere core member. I've also tried to reach out to them on IRC as well as give ML [3]. Finally, over the past few months the vsphere requirements haven't been updated [4], so they are back-leveled on their neutron-lib version.


With that in mind, IMHO we should just move forward.
When/if that project decides to engage they can rebase my lib consumption patches and easily get up to speed.



[1] http://codesearch.openstack.org/?q=rpc%5C.(ALLOWED_EXMODS%7CEXTRA_EXMODS%7Cadd_extra_exmods%7Cclear_extra_exmods%7Cget_allowed_exmods%7CVoidConnection)
[2] https://review.openstack.org/#/c/534445/
[3] http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack-dev/2018-February/127581.html
[4] https://github.com/openstack/networking-vsphere/blob/master/requirements.txt"}, {'account_id': 9656, 'date': '2018-02-23 16:42:51.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 6: Code-Review+2

revisions:
[{'created': '2018-01-12 21:35:08.000000000', 'message': 'remove unused common rpc apis

Today neutron.common.rpc has a handful of public constants and functions
that are not used outside of neutron. This patch removes those not
externally used and enhances the rpc.init function to accept extra
RPC exception modules (though it's not used today) to still support
the notion of "extra mods" for RPC.

This patch also paves the way for easier rehoming the module to
neutron-lib.

To verify there are no public consumers have a look at [1] W/R/T
networking projects.

[1] http://codesearch.openstack.org/?q=rpc%5C.(ALLOWED_EXMODS%7CEXTRA_EX
MODS%7Cadd_extra_exmods%7Cclear_extra_exmods%7Cget_allowed_exmods%7CVoid
Connection)

commit_message:
remove unused common rpc apis

Today neutron.common.rpc has a handful of public constants and functions
that are not used outside of neutron. This patch removes those not
externally used and enhances the rpc.init function to accept extra
RPC exception modules (though it's not used today) to still support
the notion of "extra mods" for RPC.

This patch also paves the way for easier rehoming the module to
neutron-lib.

Change-Id: I51607216a39980c17807dcccace3ab66b549607b

commit_message:
Fix use of tags with overcloud post configure

When specifying tags with 'kayobe overcloud post configure --tags <tags>', the
expected plays typically do not run. This seems to be due to an ansible bug,
where if a dynamically created group is referenced before creation, it will
remain empty. See https://github.com/ansible/ansible/issues/20360.

This change works around this issue by modifying the name of the dynamic groups
used in the post configure playbooks to be unique to each playbook.

Fixes: #138
(cherry picked from commit 77a41a9d0a37acd2d4c25bd7d969d965a9552428)

Change-Id: I7a884f538cfeba9d6b4b990ec445b5ad6f914193

commit_message:
Convert role to use a common systemd init role

This removes the systemd service templates and tasks from this role and
leverages a common systemd service role instead. This change removes a
lot of code duplication across all roles all without sacrificing features
or functionality. The intention of this change is to ensure uniformity and
reduce the maintenance burden on the community when sweeping changes are
needed.

In converting this role to use the common systemd_service role a
keystone_service dictionary was created in the defaults main.yml file.
This change follows the pattern of other services.

Change-Id: I70e1f6007d9f88f05ccdc737b210415274580a46
Signed-off-by: Kevin Carter <kevin.carter@rackspace.com>

https://github.com/openstack/mistral/blob/master/mistral/engine/action_handler.py#L53"}, {'account_id': 8731, 'date': '2018-02-27 11:23:35.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 4: Code-Review-1

(2 comments)

Ok, I now understand the problem finally. I really believe that the commit message could be more straightforward :) "false positive retrying" looks confusing to me. As a matter of fact, the issue is that Mistral ignores when we try to update the state of the same action multiple times even after it switched to a terminal state (ERROR in our example).

I just think that the exception should be different, something like InputException or simply ValueError because, in fact, we deal with the wrong user input in this case.

But overall the change is fine. Just please try to deliver the message to others better about why you make a change and how your fix solves the problem.

commit_message:
Prevent a action completion multiple times

If action is completed for second time we must raise and propagate
exception to the client to prevent task completion twice.

Change-Id: I36c5a85da4549ecdf97f6b5996ba436f153dabe8
Closes-Bug: 1743662
Signed-off-by: Vitalii Solodilov <mcdkr@yandex.ru>

(1 comment)

I was perhaps a little confused when writing the commit message and comments in this patch.

The goal was to address [1] i.e. not expanding the acceptor namespace prematurely. My confusion was thinking that object updates would be redirected until the acceptor namespace was expanded, which does not currently appear to be the case (although it is reasonable to think that it might become the case).

The expanding state does help with, but not completely fix, [2] i.e. donor objects being treted as misplaced. We may need a different more comprehensive fix for that, in which case it might be that the expanding state becomes unnecessary... that question is tracked here [3].

[1] https://trello.com/c/QlQfqBS1
[2] https://trello.com/c/xO8T3KiO
[3] https://trello.com/c/JdkjxkAc'}]
revisions:
[{'created': '2018-03-09 17:17:14.000000000', 'message': "Add EXPANDING state to ShardRange

Prematurely expanding an acceptor's namespace and bumping its
timestamp [1] was a terrible idea. The acceptor might send this
expanded namespace to other replicas of the root container before the
leader root has replicated the original acceptor namespace with the
same bumped timestamp. This results in the acceptor namespace being
expanded in the root before the donor has cleaved and before the donor
is deleted from the root!

The goal of expanding the acceptor's namespace was to prevent object
updates redirected from the donor during shrinking being considered as
misplaced.  This patch takes a different approach and introduces an
EXPANDING state. Now the acceptor's namespace is left unchanged until
shrinking completes, but its state is moved to EXPANDING. Then, when
shrinking completes, the donor forwards an updated acceptor shard
range to the acceptor which moves it back to ACTIVE state.

This also helps avoid a similar problem when shrinking the final shard
to the root: the root considers itself sharded while it has shard
ranges, so considers any object misplaced and was prone to moving
objects that the final shard range was in the process of cleaving to
the root. Now the root is also put into EXPANDING state when accepting
the final shrinking shard range.

Note: There is still further work needed to ensure that non-leader
roots learn that they are in EXPANDING state *before* any final shard
replica cleaves to them.

[1] Ie65cd4ce0abc98452163f6acdfad3cce5cdd216f

Change-Id: I43cb6285537a24163bfe1245fe15fe1f1393294b

commit_message:
Add EXPANDING state to ShardRange

Prematurely expanding an acceptor's namespace and bumping its
timestamp [1] was a terrible idea. The acceptor might send this
expanded namespace to other replicas of the root container before the
leader root has replicated the original acceptor namespace with the
same bumped timestamp. This results in the acceptor namespace being
expanded in the root before the donor has cleaved and before the donor
is deleted from the root!

The goal of expanding the acceptor's namespace was to prevent object
updates redirected from the donor during shrinking being considered as
misplaced.  This patch takes a different approach and introduces an
EXPANDING state. Now the acceptor's namespace is left unchanged until
shrinking completes, but its state is moved to EXPANDING. Then, when
shrinking completes, the donor forwards an updated acceptor shard
range to the acceptor which moves it back to ACTIVE state.

This also helps avoid a similar problem when shrinking the final shard
to the root: the root considers itself sharded while it has shard
ranges, so considers any object misplaced and was prone to moving
objects that the final shard range was in the process of cleaving to
the root. Now the root is also put into EXPANDING state when accepting
the final shrinking shard range.

Note: There is still further work needed to ensure that non-leader
roots learn that they are in EXPANDING state *before* any final shard
replica cleaves to them.

[1] Ie65cd4ce0abc98452163f6acdfad3cce5cdd216f

Change-Id: I43cb6285537a24163bfe1245fe15fe1f1393294b

Detect openstack_release in kolla-ansible deploy-bifrost

commit_message:
Fix invalid role template generated for ComputeOvsDpdk

Previously fixed for the CephStorage and BlockStorage roles - issue also
occurs for the ComputeOvsDpdk role.
This role also uses_deprecated_params set to 'true' but doesn't have
any deprecated params; changed it to 'false' where appropriate.

Closes-Bug: 1754633
Related-Bug: 1750828

Bifrost uses the www-data user for nginx on debian/ubuntu, and nginx on
other platforms. Kolla-ansible currently uses the nginx user for all
platforms when creating a log directory. This change uses the www-data
user on debian/ubuntu when setting ownership of the bifrost nginx log
directory.

Closes-Bug: #1753750
'}]
commit_message:
Use www-data user for bifrost nginx log directory

Bifrost uses the www-data user for nginx on debian/ubuntu, and nginx on
other platforms. Kolla-ansible currently uses the nginx user for all
platforms when creating a log directory. This change uses the www-data
user on debian/ubuntu when setting ownership of the bifrost nginx log
directory.

Change-Id: I142a158b6f2e8f8a46b684267f6fbb2a6e22a259
Closes-Bug: #1753750

Madhuri,

not really sure how you've tested it.

This was a quick hack to test another patch in ironic with real HW (which it turn was aslo a hacky PoC),
and was done quite long ago, so probably some things have changed in between...

Basically, I've created a custom classic ironic driver where the console interface was overridden with a prototype of a graphical console interface for iDRAC, thus the methods in ironic virt-driver are calling standard 'console' ironic API.

More details are in my blog post https://pshchelo.github.io/vnc-in-ironic.html"}]

commit_message:
DNM PoC Enable VNC console access to Ironic nodes

This is an early prototype for vnc graphical console access to Nova
instances running on Ironic baremetal nodes.

It is really hacky for now and sole aim is to test this patch
I283ddf5aec64ae4934ec3cf63ee7e357a8a899b2 with real HW.

In general though this work depends on "VNC Graphical console" spec
being approved and implemented in Ironic and its counterpart in Nova.

Change-Id: I3e98b79e01c0b3ade5622ab058101e1348716b82
